re, Armand, Cecile, Normand, Emile, Lucien, Marcel, Rosaire, Alphonse, Henri.","French:","topographic name for someone ‘from the well’, from Old French <i>puis</i> ‘well’, with fused preposition and definite article <i>du</i> ‘from the’. Compare   Dupee  ,   Dupuie  ,   Dupuy   2, and   Wells  ."]}]},{"name":"Lucy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Old French <i>Lucie</i>, the vernacular form of   Lucia .  It is sometimes assumed that <i>Lucy</i> is a pet form of   Lucinda  , but there is no etymological justification for this assumption. It was in fairly widespread use in the Middle Ages, and increased greatly in popularity in the 18th century and again in the 1990s. In Ireland it serves as an Anglicized form of Irish Luíseach ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":20,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705201,"age":114,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Lucy Wells was born in 1435, in Bristol, Gloucestershire, England. She married Richard Amerike in 1452, in Bristol, Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1435–":"1435–Surnud","1430–1490":"1430–1490","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1473–1502":"1473–1502","1435–Female":"1435–Surnud","1502":"1502","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1430":"1430","1473":"1473","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Bristol, Avon, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1435–":"1435–Kuollut","1430–1490":"1430–1490","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1473–1502":"1473–1502","1435–Female":"1435–Kuollut","1502":"1502","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1430":"1430","1473":"1473","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Bristol, Avon, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1435–":"1435–Décédée","1430–1490":"1430–1490","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1473–1502":"1473–1502","1435–Female":"1435–Décédée","1502":"1502","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1430":"1430","1473":"1473","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Bristol, Avon, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lady Lucy Wells est née en 1435, à Bristol, Gloucestershire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Richard Amerike en 1452, à Bristol, Gloucestershire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 2 filles. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1435–":"1435–Verstorben","1430–1490":"1430–1490","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1473–1502":"1473–1502","1435–Female":"1435–Verstorben","1502":"1502","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1430":"1430","1473":"1473","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Bristol, Avon, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Lady Lucy Wells wurde 1435 in Bristol, Gloucestershire, England geboren. Sie 